 Members" "<img class=\"face\" src=\"http://planet.ubuntu.com/heads/andregondim.png\" alt=\"\">\n<p>Hi Folks,</p>\n<p>I want to announce the latest changes in Ubuntu Brazil: new Council  and new Members!</p>\n<p>== New Council ==</p>\n<p>We had changes in the previous Ubuntu Council, through an election  that had three chosen candidates:</p>\n<p>&gt; <a title=\"André Gondim\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~andregondim\" target=\"_blank\">André Gondim</a><br />\n&gt; <a title=\"Fábio Nogueira\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~deb-user-ba\" target=\"_blank\">Fábio Nogueira</a><br />\n&gt; <a title=\"Laudeci\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~laudeci\" target=\"_blank\">Laudeci Oliveira – Pretto</a></p>\n<p>One, out of three, was re-elected, Fábio Nogueira.</p>\n<p>In this process, every candidate listed his plans if elected, and the  election consisted of three phases. In each phase, Brazilian official  members voted, selecting one Council member per round. The first  elected was<a title=\"First\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~brazilianteam/+poll/conselho2009-1\" target=\"_blank\"> André Gondim</a>, followed by <a title=\"Second\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~brazilianteam/+poll/conselho2009-2\" target=\"_blank\">Fábio ogueira</a> and then <a title=\"third\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~brazilianteam/+poll/conselho2009-3\" target=\"_blank\">Laudeci  Oliveira</a>.<br />\nVery soon we intend to pub</p>\n<p>lish our ideas and what’s next to come.</p>\n<p>== New Members ==</p>\n<p>The Brazilian Community is happy to announce its two newest Ubuntu  Members: <a title=\"Coringão\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~coringao\" target=\"_blank\">Carlos “Coringão” Donizete</a> and <a title=\"Ursinh\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~ursinha\" target=\"_blank\">Ursula Junque, a.k.a. Ursinha</a>.</p>\n<p>&gt; Coringao is the owner of Ubuntu Games, he’s very active and helpful in Ubuntu Games and development of IUG (Instalador do Ubuntu Games).<br />\n&gt;<br />\n&gt; Ursinha is an active member, helping with community support and the maintenance of  Translations’s wiki. She is really helpful with new users at #ubuntu-br.<br />\n&gt;<br />\n&gt; We are so proud of you. I say that in the name of the new Brazlian Council.</p>\n<p>Welcome!</p>\n<p>Hugs and Good Luck! <img src=\"http://en.andregondim.eti.br/../wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif\" alt=\";)\" /><br />\n<a title=\"André Gondim\" href=\"http://andregondim.eti.br/\" target=\"_blank\">My Brazilian Ubuntu Blog</a><br />\nGet involved<br />\n<a title=\"Get involved\" href=\"http://www.ubuntu.com/community/participate\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.ubuntu.com/community/participate</a></p>" "http://en.andregondim.eti.br/?p=111" (19076 51510) old 10 nil nil ((title nil "André Gondim: Brazlian Council and News Brazlian Ubuntu Members") (guid nil "http://en.andregondim.eti.br/?p=111") (link nil "http://en.andregondim.eti.br/?p=111") (description nil "\n	<img class=\"face\" src=\"http://planet.ubuntu.com/heads/andregondim.png\" alt=\"\">\n<p>Hi Folks,</p>\n<p>I want to announce the latest changes in Ubuntu Brazil: new Council  and new Members!</p>\n<p>== New Council ==</p>\n<p>We had changes in the previous Ubuntu Council, through an election  that had three chosen candidates:</p>\n<p>&gt; <a title=\"André Gondim\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~andregondim\" target=\"_blank\">André Gondim</a><br />\n&gt; <a title=\"Fábio Nogueira\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~deb-user-ba\" target=\"_blank\">Fábio Nogueira</a><br />\n&gt; <a title=\"Laudeci\" href=\"http://launchpad.net/~laudeci\" target=\"_blank\">Laudeci Oliveira &#8211; Pretto</a></p>\n<p>One, out of three, was re-elected, Fábio Nogueira.</p>\n<p>In this process, every candidate listed his plans if elected, and the  election consisted of three phases. In each phase, Brazilian official  members voted, selecting one Council member per round. The first  elected was<a title=\"First\" href=\"https://edge.launchpad.net/~braziliant