e’ve been <a href=\"http://princessleia.com/journal/?p=1806\">talking about recently</a> about <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning\">Ubuntu Learning</a>, The official community of educators who believe in education of community members and the public as a means to helping us move forwards with what we are trying to do as a community.</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://doctormo.files.wordpress.com/2009/08/ubuntu-community-branding.png?w=150&h=152\" alt=\"ubuntu-community-branding\" title=\"ubuntu-community-branding\" width=\"150\" height=\"152\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-1024\" />There are various sections and one which need some love and attention, this is for the <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics\">Community Course</a>. This is where we want to make classes to teach people how to be effective community leaders, community members, contributing members, advocates, marketers, how to get on with others, how to inspire, lead, all those lovely topics.</p>\n<p>What I need is a set of Jono Bacon followers to help out and start fleshing out and making good the topics page: <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics\">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics</a>, I’d have asked Jono Bacon himself to get involved since he’s written a book about this exact subject, but the guy is fairly busy so I’m going to call on the entire community to define what will be helpful to teaching people all aspects of being good community members.</p>\n<p>We also want to make sure the name is appropriate and that it covers the scope we want it to. There is a plan to have lots of different classes in this course. So if Spreading Ubuntu or Advocate Classes is too restrictive, we want to know if it should be simply “Community Classes” “Communing with Ubuntu”.</p>\n<p>If your interested in writing the classes for this topic, the post of Publisher/Organiser for this topic is open and we’re looking for people to come and man the pumps. Come to the IRC channel #ubuntu-learning on freenode where I have been teaching “how to create classes” and I can help you get started.</p>\n<p>Mentioning available.</p>\n<a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=doctormo.wordpress.com&amp;blog=6486156&amp;post=1023&amp;subd=doctormo&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\" /></div>" "http://doctormo.wordpress.com/2009/08/14/community-topics/" (19077 1463) old 6 nil nil ((title nil "Martin Owens: Community Topics") (guid nil "http://doctormo.wordpress.com/?p=1023") (link nil "http://doctormo.wordpress.com/2009/08/14/community-topics/") (description nil "\n	<img class=\"face\" src=\"http://planet.ubuntu.com/heads/doctormo.png\" alt=\"\">\n<div class=\"snap_preview\"><br /><p>As we&#8217;ve been <a href=\"http://princessleia.com/journal/?p=1806\">talking about recently</a> about <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning\">Ubuntu Learning</a>, The official community of educators who believe in education of community members and the public as a means to helping us move forwards with what we are trying to do as a community.</p>\n<p><img src=\"http://doctormo.files.wordpress.com/2009/08/ubuntu-community-branding.png?w=150&#038;h=152\" alt=\"ubuntu-community-branding\" title=\"ubuntu-community-branding\" width=\"150\" height=\"152\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-1024\" />There are various sections and one which need some love and attention, this is for the <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics\">Community Course</a>. This is where we want to make classes to teach people how to be effective community leaders, community members, contributing members, advocates, marketers, how to get on with others, how to inspire, lead, all those lovely topics.</p>\n<p>What I need is a set of Jono Bacon followers to help out and start fleshing out and making good the topics page: <a href=\"https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics\">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Learning/AdvocateTopics</a>, I&#8217;d have asked Jono Bacon himself to get involved since he&#8217;s written a book about this exact subject, but the guy is fairly busy so I&#8217;m going to call on the entire community to define what will be helpful to teaching people all aspects of being good community members.</p>\n<p>We also want to make sure the name is appropriate and that it covers the scope we want it to. There is a plan to have lots of different classes in this course. So if Spreading Ubuntu or Advocate Classes is too restrictive, we want to know if it should be simply &#8220;Community Classes&#8221; &#8220;Communing with Ubuntu&#8221;.</p>\n<p>If your interested in writing the classes for this topic, the post of Publisher/Organiser for this topic is open and we&#8217;re looking for people to come and man the pumps. Come to the IRC channel #ubuntu-learning on freenode where I have been teaching &#8220;how to create classes&#8221; and I can help you get started.</p>\n<p>Mentioning available.</p>\n  <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/doctormo.wordpress.com/1023/\" /></a> <img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=doctormo.wordpress.com&amp;blog=6486156&amp;post=1023&amp;subd=doctormo&amp;ref=&amp;feed=1\" /></div>	") (pubDate nil "Fri, 14 Aug 2009 06:35:35 +0000") (dc:creator nil "doctormo"))) ("Stephan Hermann: This Network Setup freaks me out" "<img class=\"face\" src=\"http://planet.ubuntu.com/heads/sh.png\" alt=\"\">\n<p>Really, this setup scares me...but strangly ubuntu just swallows it:</p>\n<p class=\"rtecenter\"><a href=\"http://www.sourcecode.de/files/image/Special/lb_setup_jpg.png\"><img height=\"453\" width=\"640\" src=\"http://www.sourcecode.de/files/image/Special/lb_setup_small.png\" alt=\"\" /></a></p>\n<pre class=\"rteindent1\">\n1: lo: &lt;LOOPBACK,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 16436 qdisc noqueue state UNKNOWN\nlink/loopback 00:00:00:00:00:00 brd 00:00:00:00:00:00\ninet 127.0.0.1/8 scope host lo\ninet6 ::1/128 scope host\nvalid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n2: eth3: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond1 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n3: eth2: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond1 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n4: eth0: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond0 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:25:b3:a4:b9:68 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n5: eth5: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond1 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n6: eth4: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond1 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n7: eth7: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond2 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n8: eth1: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond0 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:25:b3:a4:b9:68 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n9: eth6: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond2 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n10: eth9: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond2 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n11: eth8: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc pfifo_fast master bond2 state UP qlen 1000\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n12: bond0: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UP\nlink/ether 00:25:b3:a4:b9:68 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\ninet 0.0.0.1/32 brd 255.255.255.255 scope global bond0\ninet6 fe80::225:b3ff:fea4:b968/64 scope link\nvalid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n13: bond1: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue master bond3 state UP\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n14: bond2: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,SLAVE,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue master bond3 state UP\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\n15: vlan932@bond0: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UP\nlink/ether 00:25:b3:a4:b9:68 brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\ninet &lt;ip&gt;/23 brd bcast scope global vlan932\ninet6 fe80::225:b3ff:fea4:b968/64 scope link\nvalid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n16: bond3: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UP\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\ninet 0.0.0.4/32 brd 255.255.255.255 scope global bond3\ninet6 fe80::224:81ff:fe7b:3bcc/64 scope link\nvalid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n17: vlan101@bond3: &lt;BROADCAST,MULTICAST,MASTER,UP,LOWER_UP&gt; mtu 1500 qdisc noqueue state UP\nlink/ether 00:24:81:7b:3b:cc brd ff:ff:ff:ff:ff:ff\ninet &lt;ip&gt;/29 brd bcast scope global vlan101\ninet6 fe80::224:81ff:fe7b:3bcc/64 scope link tentative\nvalid_lft forever preferred_lft forever\n</pre>\n<!--\n<rdf:RDF xmlns:rdf=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#\" xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\" xmlns:trackback=\"http://madskills.com/public/xml/rss/module/trackback/\">\n<rdf:Description rdf:about=\"http://www.sourcecode.de/content/network-setup-freaks-me-out\" dc:identifier=\"http://www.sourcecode.de/content/network-setup-freaks-me-out\" dc:title=\"This Network Setup freaks me out\" trackback:ping=\"http://www.sourcecode.de/trackback/1231\" />\n</rdf:RDF>\n-->" "http://www.sourcecode.de/content/network-setup-freaks-me-out" (19077 13662) old 5 nil nil ((title nil "Stephan Hermann: This Network Setup freaks me out") (guid nil "http://www.sourcecode.de/feeds/shermann/ubuntu/1231 at http://www.sourcecode.de") (link nil "http://www.sourcecode.de/content/network-setup-freaks-me-out") (description nil "\n	<img cla